\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Square brackets are used to provide commentary when quoting an original source. For example, adding an extra word within a quote to provide better clarity, such as with this quote. I have left my contribution unitalicised to further state it\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s not part of the original quote:}
